def: The celebrated war horse of Alexander the Great.
Like a lath; long and slender.A lathy horse, all legs and length. R. Browning.
Destitute of shape or regular form; wanting symmetry ofdimensions; misshapen; -- opposed to Ant: shapely.-- Shape"less*ness, n.The shapeless rock, or hanging precipice. Pope.

A curve whose contact with a given curve, at a given point, isof a higher order (or involves the equality of a greater number ofsuccessive differential coefficients of the ordinates of the curvestaken at that point) than that of any other curve of the same kind.
Resting satisfied or submissive; disposed tacitly to submit;assentive; as, an acquiescent policy.
To think out; to find out or discover by thinking; to devise;to contrive. "Excogitate strange arts." Stirling.This evidence . . . thus excogitated out of the general theory.Whewell.
Unless; except; -- introducing a clause.You will never live to my age without you keep yourselves in breathwith exercise, and in heart with joyfulness. Sir P. Sidney.
[Fraise a kind of defense; also Friz.) A kind of small ruffle.Halliwell.
A soldier of light cavalry of the 16th century, who carried ademilance.
